        "id": 2865575,
        "name": "Brian S t o t t e r",
        "username": "Brian_S_t_o_t_t_e_r",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/brian_s_t_o_t_t_e_r/{size}/2486_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-04-14T23:47:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3377385&amp;iNote=8308888\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2012 Delamotte Champagne Blanc de Blancs Mill\u00e9sim\u00e9</strong></a> <em>- France, Champagne (4/14/2020)</em><br>\nPop n\u2019 pour in GGG glass. Plenty of fine bubbles and a medium-sized mousse that quickly dissipates. Slightly bruised yellow apple, lemon/lime, and a core of seashell/chalky minerality. A little bready note on the palate after the Champagne gets to close to room temperature. Lovely acidity, very refreshing on the palate. A little coiled up right now, will check on my next bottle in 5 years. <em><strong>(91 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
