      {
        "id": 3049225,
        "name": "Brian G r a f s t r o m",
        "username": "Brian_G_r_a_f_s_t_r_o_m",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/brian_g_r_a_f_s_t_r_o_m/{size}/98878_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-12-17T00:15:55.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3377385&amp;iNote=8830467\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2012 Delamotte Champagne Blanc de Blancs Mill\u00e9sim\u00e9</strong></a> <em>- France, Champagne (11/6/2020)</em><br>\n\u2013 tasted non-blind over approx. 1.5 hours \u2013</p>\n<p>NOSE: Light and airy; mango; kiwi fruit.</p>\n<p>BODY: light bodied; airy mouthfeel.</p>\n<p>TASTE: high acidity; crisp; a touch creamy (oaky?); bit of mango. Overall, quite nice \u2014 a bit reserved today, but seems to have the stuffing to develop nicely over the short term. I subsequently purchased three more bottles. Gut impression score: low 90s.</p>",
